# Challenges and Solutions

During the development of the Drive-by-Wire system, several mechanical and electrical challenges were encountered. 
This document summarizes the key issues faced and the solutions implemented.

---

## 1. Chassis Assembly Issues
### Problem
Finding suitable screws for the chassis was difficult. 
Several screws did not fit properly or caused alignment issues.

---

## 2. Wheel Rotation Issues
### Problem
The wheels were not spinning freely when mounted on the 3D printed parts. 
This caused friction and restricted vehicle movement.
This issue was only in the front wheels.

### Solution
We scraped the insides of the 3D printed part which holds the BO Wheels. 

---

## 3. Battery Power Issues

### Problem
Lithium-ion batteries occasionally lost power or stopped working during operation. 
This affected system reliability.

### Solution
We bought more reliable - branded batteries

---

## Learning Outcomes

These challenges provided practical experience in:

- Mechanical troubleshooting
- Hardware reliability improvement
- Electrical power stability management
- Iterative design and testing
